  "prompt": "How can I learn to write better essays?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to improve your essay writing:\n\n1. Read extensively\n- Read high-quality writing across different genres\n- Analyze how good writers structure their arguments\n\n2. Practice basic writing skills\n- Learn proper grammar and punctuation\n- Develop clear, concise sentence structure\n- Expand your vocabulary\n\n3. Understand essay structure\n- Create clear thesis statements\n- Use logical paragraph organization\n- Include strong introductions and conclusions\n\n4. Research effectively\n- Use credible sources\n- Take good notes\n- Cite sources properly\n\n5. Plan before writing\n- Outline your main points\n- Create a rough draft\n- Organize your thoughts systematically\n\n6. Edit and revise\n- Review your first draft critically\n- Check for clarity and coherence\n- Proofread carefully\n\n7. Learn from feedback\n- Ask teachers or peers to review your work\n- Be open to constructive criticism\n- Implement suggested improvements\n\n8. Study essay writing techniques\n- Take writing workshops\n- Use online resources and tutorials\n- Read writing guides\n\n9. Practice consistently\n- Write regularly\n- Try different essay styles and topics\n- Challenge yourself to improve\n\n10. Develop critical thinking skills\n- Analyze arguments\n- Consider multiple perspectives\n- Form well-reasoned conclusions",
